Sure! You can implement deceleration by gradually reducing the character's velocity when no input is detected. For example, in your Update method, check if movement input is zero, then apply a damping factor to your velocity vector. Here's a simple snippet:

```csharp
if (input == Vector3.zero) {
    velocity = Vector3.Lerp(velocity, Vector3.zero, decelerationRate * Time.deltaTime);
}
```

This smoothly slows the character down. Adjust 'decelerationRate' to control how quickly the character stops. Would you like me to help integrate this into your existing script?
